owl:NamedIndividual.terms:title: Dublin Core Metadata Element Set, Version 1.1

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: The guidelines for using names of persons or organizations as creators also apply to contributors. Typically, the name of a Contributor should be used to indicate the entity.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: An entity responsible for making contributions to the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Contributor
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: A [second property](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/#http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor) with the same name as this property has been declared in the [dcterms: namespace](http://purl.org/dc/terms/). See the Introduction to the document [DCMI Metadata Terms](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/) for an explanation.

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Spatial topic and spatial applicability may be a named place or a location specified by its geographic coordinates. Temporal topic may be a named period, date, or date range. A jurisdiction may be a named administrative entity or a geographic place to which the resource applies. Recommended practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names [[TGN](https://www.getty.edu/research/tools/vocabulary/tgn/index.html)]. Where appropriate, named places or time periods may be used in preference to numeric identifiers such as sets of coordinates or date ranges.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The spatial or temporal topic of the resource, spatial applicability of the resource, or jurisdiction under which the resource is relevant.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Coverage
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: A [second property](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/#http://purl.org/dc/terms/coverage) with the same name as this property has been declared in the [dcterms: namespace](http://purl.org/dc/terms/). See the Introduction to the document [DCMI Metadata Terms](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/) for an explanation.

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Description may include but is not limited to: an abstract, a table of contents, a graphical representation, or a free-text account of the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: An account of the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Description
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: A [second property](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/#http://purl.org/dc/terms/description) with the same name as this property has been declared in the [dcterms: namespace](http://purl.org/dc/terms/). See the Introduction to the document [DCMI Metadata Terms](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/) for an explanation.

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Recommended practice is to use a controlled vocabulary where available. For example, for file formats one could use the list of Internet Media Types [[MIME](https://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml)].
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The file format, physical medium, or dimensions of the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Format
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: A [second property](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/#http://purl.org/dc/terms/format) with the same name as this property has been declared in the [dcterms: namespace](http://purl.org/dc/terms/). See the Introduction to the document [DCMI Metadata Terms](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/) for an explanation.

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Recommended practice is to identify the resource by means of a string conforming to an identification system.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: An unambiguous reference to the resource within a given context.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Identifier
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: A [second property](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/#http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier) with the same name as this property has been declared in the [dcterms: namespace](http://purl.org/dc/terms/). See the Introduction to the document [DCMI Metadata Terms](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/) for an explanation.

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Recommended practice is to use either a non-literal value representing a language from a controlled vocabulary such as ISO 639-2 or ISO 639-3, or a literal value consisting of an IETF Best Current Practice 47 [[IETF-BCP47](https://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47)] language tag.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A language of the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Language
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: A [second property](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/#http://purl.org/dc/terms/language) with the same name as this property has been declared in the [dcterms: namespace](http://purl.org/dc/terms/). See the Introduction to the document [DCMI Metadata Terms](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/) for an explanation.

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Examples of a Publisher include a person, an organization, or a service. Typically, the name of a Publisher should be used to indicate the entity.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: An entity responsible for making the resource available.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Publisher
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: A [second property](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/#http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher) with the same name as this property has been declared in the [dcterms: namespace](http://purl.org/dc/terms/). See the Introduction to the document [DCMI Metadata Terms](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/) for an explanation.

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Recommended practice is to identify the related resource by means of a URI. If this is not possible or feasible, a string conforming to a formal identification system may be provided.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A related resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Relation
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: A [second property](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/#http://purl.org/dc/terms/relation) with the same name as this property has been declared in the [dcterms: namespace](http://purl.org/dc/terms/). See the Introduction to the document [DCMI Metadata Terms](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/) for an explanation.

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Typically, rights information includes a statement about various property rights associated with the resource, including intellectual property rights.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Information about rights held in and over the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Rights
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: A [second property](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/#http://purl.org/dc/terms/rights) with the same name as this property has been declared in the [dcterms: namespace](http://purl.org/dc/terms/). See the Introduction to the document [DCMI Metadata Terms](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/) for an explanation.

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: The described resource may be derived from the related resource in whole or in part. Recommended best practice is to identify the related resource by means of a string conforming to a formal identification system.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A related resource from which the described resource is derived.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Source
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: A [second property](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/#http://purl.org/dc/terms/source) with the same name as this property has been declared in the [dcterms: namespace](http://purl.org/dc/terms/). See the Introduction to the document [DCMI Metadata Terms](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/) for an explanation.

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Typically, the subject will be represented using keywords, key phrases, or classification codes. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The topic of the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Subject
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: A [second property](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/#http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject) with the same name as this property has been declared in the [dcterms: namespace](http://purl.org/dc/terms/). See the Introduction to the document [DCMI Metadata Terms](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/) for an explanation.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A name given to the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Title
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: A [second property](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/#http://purl.org/dc/terms/title) with the same name as this property has been declared in the [dcterms: namespace](http://purl.org/dc/terms/). See the Introduction to the document [DCMI Metadata Terms](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/) for an explanation.

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Recommended practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the DCMI Type Vocabulary [[DCMI-TYPE](http://dublincore.org/documents/dcmi-type-vocabulary/)]. To describe the file format, physical medium, or dimensions of the resource, use the Format element.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The nature or genre of the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Type
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: A [second property](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/#http://purl.org/dc/terms/type) with the same name as this property has been declared in the [dcterms: namespace](http://purl.org/dc/terms/). See the Introduction to the document [DCMI Metadata Terms](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/) for an explanation.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The set of classes specified by the DCMI Type Vocabulary, used to categorize the nature or genre of the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: DCMI Type Vocabulary

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The set of conceptual resources specified by the Dewey Decimal Classification.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: DDC

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The set of media types specified by the Internet Assigned Numbers Authority.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: IMT

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The set of conceptual resources specified by the Library of Congress Classification.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: LCC

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The set of labeled concepts specified by the Library of Congress Subject Headings.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: LCSH

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The set of labeled concepts specified by the Medical Subject Headings.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: MeSH

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The set of conceptual resources specified by the National Library of Medicine Classification.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: NLM

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The set of places specified by the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: TGN

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The set of conceptual resources specified by the Universal Decimal Classification.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: UDC

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A summary of the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Abstract

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Access Rights may include information regarding access or restrictions based on privacy, security, or other policies.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Information about who access the resource or an indication of its security status.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Access Rights

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Recommended practice is to use this property with non-literal values from a vocabulary of audience types.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A class of agents for whom the resource is intended or useful.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Audience

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: An established standard to which the described resource conforms.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Conforms To

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Spatial topic and spatial applicability may be a named place or a location specified by its geographic coordinates. Temporal topic may be a named period, date, or date range. A jurisdiction may be a named administrative entity or a geographic place to which the resource applies. Recommended practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names [[TGN](https://www.getty.edu/research/tools/vocabulary/tgn/index.html)]. Where appropriate, named places or time periods may be used in preference to numeric identifiers such as sets of coordinates or date ranges. Because coverage is so broadly defined, it is preferable to use the more specific subproperties Temporal Coverage and Spatial Coverage.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The spatial or temporal topic of the resource, spatial applicability of the resource, or jurisdiction under which the resource is relevant.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Coverage

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Recommended practice is to identify the creator with a URI. If this is not possible or feasible, a literal value that identifies the creator may be provided.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: An entity responsible for making the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Creator

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A class of agents, defined in terms of progression through an educational or training context, for which the described resource is intended.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Audience Education Level

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Recommended practice is to specify the file size in megabytes and duration in ISO 8601 format.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The size or duration of the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Extent

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Recommended practice is to use a controlled vocabulary where available. For example, for file formats one could use the list of Internet Media Types [[MIME](https://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml)]. Examples of dimensions include size and duration.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The file format, physical medium, or dimensions of the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Format

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: This property is intended to be used with non-literal values. This property is an inverse property of Is Format Of.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A related resource that is substantially the same as the pre-existing described resource, but in another format.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Has Format

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: This property is intended to be used with non-literal values. This property is an inverse property of Is Part Of.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A related resource that is included either physically or logically in the described resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Has Part

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Changes in version imply substantive changes in content rather than differences in format. This property is intended to be used with non-literal values. This property is an inverse property of Is Version Of.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A related resource that is a version, edition, or adaptation of the described resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Has Version

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Instructional Method typically includes ways of presenting instructional materials or conducting instructional activities, patterns of learner-to-learner and learner-to-instructor interactions, and mechanisms by which group and individual levels of learning are measured. Instructional methods include all aspects of the instruction and learning processes from planning and implementation through evaluation and feedback.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A process, used to engender knowledge, attitudes and skills, that the described resource is designed to support.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Instructional Method

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: This property is intended to be used with non-literal values. This property is an inverse property of Has Format.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A pre-existing related resource that is substantially the same as the described resource, but in another format.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Is Format Of

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: This property is intended to be used with non-literal values. This property is an inverse property of Has Part.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A related resource in which the described resource is physically or logically included.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Is Part Of

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: This property is intended to be used with non-literal values. This property is an inverse property of References.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A related resource that references, cites, or otherwise points to the described resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Is Referenced By

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: This property is intended to be used with non-literal values. This property is an inverse property of Replaces.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A related resource that supplants, displaces, or supersedes the described resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Is Replaced By

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: This property is intended to be used with non-literal values. This property is an inverse property of Requires.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A related resource that requires the described resource to support its function, delivery, or coherence.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Is Required By

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Changes in version imply substantive changes in content rather than differences in format. This property is intended to be used with non-literal values. This property is an inverse property of Has Version.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A related resource of which the described resource is a version, edition, or adaptation.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Is Version Of

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Recommended practice is to use either a non-literal value representing a language from a controlled vocabulary such as ISO 639-2 or ISO 639-3, or a literal value consisting of an IETF Best Current Practice 47 [[IETF-BCP47](https://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47)] language tag.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A language of the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Language

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Recommended practice is to identify the license document with a URI. If this is not possible or feasible, a literal value that identifies the license may be provided.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A legal document giving official permission to do something with the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: License

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: In an educational context, a mediator might be a parent, teacher, teaching assistant, or care-giver.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: An entity that mediates access to the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Mediator

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The material or physical carrier of the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Medium

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: The statement may include a description of any changes successive custodians made to the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A statement of any changes in ownership and custody of the resource since its creation that are significant for its authenticity, integrity, and interpretation.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Provenance

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: This property is intended to be used with non-literal values. This property is an inverse property of Is Referenced By.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A related resource that is referenced, cited, or otherwise pointed to by the described resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: References

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Recommended practice is to identify the related resource by means of a URI. If this is not possible or feasible, a string conforming to a formal identification system may be provided.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A related resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Relation

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: This property is intended to be used with non-literal values. This property is an inverse property of Is Replaced By.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A related resource that is supplanted, displaced, or superseded by the described resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Replaces

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: This property is intended to be used with non-literal values. This property is an inverse property of Is Required By.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A related resource that is required by the described resource to support its function, delivery, or coherence.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Requires

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Typically, rights information includes a statement about various property rights associated with the resource, including intellectual property rights. Recommended practice is to refer to a rights statement with a URI. If this is not possible or feasible, a literal value (name, label, or short text) may be provided.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Information about rights held in and over the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Rights

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Recommended practice is to refer to the rights holder with a URI. If this is not possible or feasible, a literal value that identifies the rights holder may be provided.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A person or organization owning or managing rights over the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Rights Holder

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: This property is intended to be used with non-literal values. The described resource may be derived from the related resource in whole or in part. Best practice is to identify the related resource by means of a URI or a string conforming to a formal identification system.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A related resource from which the described resource is derived.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Source

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Spatial characteristics of the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Spatial Coverage

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Recommended practice is to refer to the subject with a URI. If this is not possible or feasible, a literal value that identifies the subject may be provided. Both should preferably refer to a subject in a controlled vocabulary.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A topic of the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Subject

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A list of subunits of the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Table Of Contents

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Temporal characteristics of the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Temporal Coverage

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: Recommended practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the DCMI Type Vocabulary [[DCMI-TYPE](http://dublincore.org/documents/dcmi-type-vocabulary/)]. To describe the file format, physical medium, or dimensions of the resource, use the property Format.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The nature or genre of the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Type

rdf:Description.terms:description: Examples of a Creator include a person, an organization, or a service. Typically, the name of a Creator should be used to indicate the entity.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An entity primarily responsible for making the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Creator
rdf:Description.skos:note: A [second property](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/#http://purl.org/dc/terms/creator) with the same name as this property has been declared in the [dcterms: namespace](http://purl.org/dc/terms/). See the Introduction to the document [DCMI Metadata Terms](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/) for an explanation.

rdf:Description.terms:description: Date may be used to express temporal information at any level of granularity. Recommended practice is to express the date, date/time, or period of time according to ISO 8601-1 [[ISO 8601-1](https://www.iso.org/iso-8601-date-and-time-format.html)] or a published profile of the ISO standard, such as the W3C Note on Date and Time Formats [[W3CDTF](https://www.w3.org/TR/NOTE-datetime)] or the Extended Date/Time Format Specification [[EDTF](http://www.loc.gov/standards/datetime/)]. If the full date is unknown, month and year (YYYY-MM) or just year (YYYY) may be used. Date ranges may be specified using ISO 8601 period of time specification in which start and end dates are separated by a '/' (slash) character. Either the start or end date may be missing.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A point or period of time associated with an event in the lifecycle of the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Date
rdf:Description.skos:note: A [second property](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/#http://purl.org/dc/terms/date) with the same name as this property has been declared in the [dcterms: namespace](http://purl.org/dc/terms/). See the Introduction to the document [DCMI Metadata Terms](/specifications/dublin-core/dcmi-terms/) for an explanation.

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A resource that acts or has the power to act.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Agent

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A group of agents.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Agent Class

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A book, article, or other documentary resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Bibliographic Resource

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of regions in space defined by their geographic coordinates according to the DCMI Box Encoding Scheme.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: DCMI Box

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A digital resource format.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: File Format

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A rate at which something recurs.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Frequency

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of codes listed in ISO 3166-1 for the representation of names of countries.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ISO 3166

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The three-letter alphabetic codes listed in ISO639-2 for the representation of names of languages.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ISO 639-2

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of three-letter codes listed in ISO 639-3 for the representation of names of languages.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ISO 639-3

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The extent or range of judicial, law enforcement, or other authority.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Jurisdiction

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A legal document giving official permission to do something with a resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: License Document

rdf:Description.terms:description: Written, spoken, sign, and computer languages are linguistic systems.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A system of signs, symbols, sounds, gestures, or rules used in communication.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Linguistic System

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A spatial region or named place.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Location

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A location, period of time, or jurisdiction.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Location, Period, or Jurisdiction

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A file format or physical medium.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Media Type

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A media type or extent.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Media Type or Extent

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A method by which resources are added to a collection.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Method of Accrual

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A process that is used to engender knowledge, attitudes, and skills.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Method of Instruction

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of time intervals defined by their limits according to the DCMI Period Encoding Scheme.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: DCMI Period

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An interval of time that is named or defined by its start and end dates.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Period of Time

rdf:Description.terms:description: Examples include paper, canvas, or DVD.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A physical material or carrier.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Physical Medium

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A material thing.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Physical Resource

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of points in space defined by their geographic coordinates according to the DCMI Point Encoding Scheme.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: DCMI Point

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A plan or course of action by an authority, intended to influence and determine decisions, actions, and other matters.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Policy

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Any changes in ownership and custody of a resource since its creation that are significant for its authenticity, integrity, and interpretation.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Provenance Statement

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of tags, constructed according to RFC 1766, for the identification of languages.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: RFC 1766

rdf:Description.terms:description: RFC 3066 has been obsoleted by RFC 4646.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of tags constructed according to RFC 3066 for the identification of languages.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: RFC 3066

rdf:Description.terms:description: RFC 4646 obsoletes RFC 3066.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of tags constructed according to RFC 4646 for the identification of languages.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: RFC 4646

rdf:Description.terms:description: RFC 5646 obsoletes RFC 4646.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of tags constructed according to RFC 5646 for the identification of languages.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: RFC 5646

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A statement about the intellectual property rights (IPR) held in or over a resource, a legal document giving official permission to do something with a resource, or a statement about access rights.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Rights Statement

rdf:Description.terms:description: Examples include a number of pages, a specification of length, width, and breadth, or a period in hours, minutes, and seconds.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A dimension or extent, or a time taken to play or execute.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Size or Duration

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference point against which other things can be evaluated or compared.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Standard

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of identifiers constructed according to the generic syntax for Uniform Resource Identifiers as specified by the Internet Engineering Task Force.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: URI

rdf:Description.terms:description: The guidelines for using names of persons or organizations as creators apply to contributors.

rdf:Description.terms:description: Recommended practice is to describe the date, date/time, or period of time as recommended for the property Date, of which this is a subproperty.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Date of creation of the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Date Created

rdf:Description.terms:description: Date may be used to express temporal information at any level of granularity. Recommended practice is to express the date, date/time, or period of time according to ISO 8601-1 [[ISO 8601-1](https://www.iso.org/iso-8601-date-and-time-format.html)] or a published profile of the ISO standard, such as the W3C Note on Date and Time Formats [[W3CDTF](https://www.w3.org/TR/NOTE-datetime)] or the Extended Date/Time Format Specification [[EDTF](http://www.loc.gov/standards/datetime/)]. If the full date is unknown, month and year (YYYY-MM) or just year (YYYY) may be used. Date ranges may be specified using ISO 8601 period of time specification in which start and end dates are separated by a '/' (slash) character. Either the start or end date may be missing.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A point or period of time associated with an event in the lifecycle of the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Date

rdf:Description.terms:description: Recommended practice is to describe the date, date/time, or period of time as recommended for the property Date, of which this is a subproperty. Examples of resources to which a date of acceptance may be relevant are a thesis (accepted by a university department) or an article (accepted by a journal).
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Date of acceptance of the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Date Accepted

rdf:Description.terms:description: Typically a year. Recommended practice is to describe the date, date/time, or period of time as recommended for the property Date, of which this is a subproperty.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Date of copyright of the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Date Copyrighted

rdf:Description.terms:description: Recommended practice is to describe the date, date/time, or period of time as recommended for the property Date, of which this is a subproperty. Examples of resources to which a 'Date Submitted' may be relevant include a thesis (submitted to a university department) or an article (submitted to a journal).
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Date of submission of the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Date Submitted

owl:AnnotationProperty.terms:description: Description may include but is not limited to: an abstract, a table of contents, a graphical representation, or a free-text account of the resource.

rdf:Description.terms:description: Recommended practice is to identify the resource by means of a string conforming to an identification system. Examples include International Standard Book Number (ISBN), Digital Object Identifier (DOI), and Uniform Resource Name (URN). Persistent identifiers should be provided as HTTP URIs.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An unambiguous reference to the resource within a given context.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Identifier
